   Technology Strategies [dot-blue.gif]
   [whitedot.gif]

   Technology Strategies NASA's Technology Portal is a gateway to
   innovative technologies across NASA.

   The NASA Technology Plan describes an investment in NASA's future.

   The Space Science Enterprise Integrated Technology Strategy is now
   online. Learn fascinating facts about our technology programs.
   [whitedot.gif]
   [whitedot.gif]
   Transportation and Mobility [dot-blue.gif]
   [whitedot.gif]

   Transportation and Mobility Transportation and Mobility details
   technologies used to impel and maneuver spacecraft. It examines such
   criteria as aerocapture, descent onto a surface, mobility at the
   destination (as in the case of rovers), and sample return.
   [whitedot.gif]
   [whitedot.gif]
   Sample Acquisition and Return [dot-blue.gif]
   [whitedot.gif]

   Sample Acquisition and Return Sample Acquisition and Return describes
   the emerging science of obtaining non-terrestrial materials and
   transporting them back to Earth for analysis. Technologies used in
   surface penetration, collection, shipping and handling are explained.

                                 Back to top
   [whitedot.gif]
   [whitedot.gif]
   Power [dot-blue.gif]
   [whitedot.gif]

   Power Power for spacecraft and small surface vehicles is detailed in
   this section. Technologies used in specialized batteries, generators,
   solar arrays as well as other forms of solar electric propulsion are
   described in detail.
   [whitedot.gif]
   [whitedot.gif]
   Science Instruments [dot-blue.gif]
   [whitedot.gif]

   Science Instruments Science Instruments are the detectors which let
   scientists understand properties of the bodies and phenomena being
   explored. They range from seismic stations (in the case of a
   solid-surface lander) to instruments which study atmospheres.
   [whitedot.gif]
   [whitedot.gif]
   Communications [dot-blue.gif]
   [whitedot.gif]

   GRAPHIC Communications examines methods by which scientists send and
   receive information to and from spacecraft. Various technologies are
   explained, such as those used in Earth receive stations, radio systems,
   specialized antennas, in situ communication systems, among many others.

                                 Back to top
   [whitedot.gif]
   [whitedot.gif]
   Operability [dot-blue.gif]
   [whitedot.gif]

   Operability Operability outlines the workings of a Solar Distributed
   System. Autonomous flight systems, precision navigation and flight
   information systems contribute to a mission's operability.
   [whitedot.gif]
   [whitedot.gif]
   Technology Validation [dot-blue.gif]
   [whitedot.gif]

   Technology Validation Technology Validation is a process of validating
   each of the above listed technology types.
   [whitedot.gif]
   [whitedot.gif]
   Technology Programs [dot-blue.gif]
   [whitedot.gif]

   Technology Programs Technology Programs lists the funded development
   initiatives for technology within the NASA program which support Solar
   System Exploration missions.

